original: Kjellberg, Knut Gunnar Kison, as–suransdirektör, konsul, kapten, Göteborg, f. 1/2/96 i Sthlm av prof. Knut K. Oi. h. h; f. von Bahr. G. 26 m. Elizabeth Tietgens. Barn: Barbro Gunnarsdotter f. 29. — Stud:ex., DHS, re:s:off:ex. Re^s. t. flert. europ. länder uppr. ggr samt t. Holl. o. Britt. Ind., Kina, Filippinerna, Siam o. Japan. Anst. v. A-B Transmarina Komp. i Sthlm 19-20, i Hamburg 21, J. A. Kjellberg & Söner i London 22, Paris 23, på lava 24-26, i Kina 27-28 samt i Gbg 29-33, dir. i Sjöförsäkr. A-B Gauthiod i Gbg ^sed. 34 o. i Sv:e’s Allm. Sjöförsäkr. A-B sed. 46. Medl. av sällsk. Gnistan, Börssällsk., SHT m. fl.
translated: Kjellberg, Knut Gunnar Kison, insurance director, consul, captain, Gothenburg, b. 1/2/96 in Stockholm, son of Professor Knut K. Oi. h. h; f. von Bahr. Married on 26 to Elizabeth Tietgens. Children: Barbro Gunnarsdotter b. 29. Completed secondary school exam, DHS, and reserve officer exam. Traveled to several European countries on multiple occasions, as well as to the Netherlands, British India, China, the Philippines, Siam, and Japan. Employed by Transmarina Company in Stockholm from 1919-1920, in Hamburg in 1921, J. A. Kjellberg & Sons in London in 1922, Paris in 1923, on lava from 1924-1926, in China from 1927-1928, and in Gothenburg from 1929-1933. Director of Gauthiod Marine Insurance Company in Gothenburg since 1934 and of Sweden's General Marine Insurance Company since 1946. Member of the societies Gnistan, Börssällsk., SHT, and others.
